In your strong and powerful name, amen.

19:35.445 --> 19:36.787
Church, thanks for singing with us.

19:36.807 --> 19:38.130
You can go ahead and take a seat.

19:42.562 --> 19:44.568
Hey everyone and welcome to Eaglebrook Church.

19:44.688 --> 19:45.671
My name is Jeff Dodge.

19:45.912 --> 19:50.446
I am the online campus pastor and last weekend was one that I will never forget.

19:50.626 --> 19:54.397
Like maybe one of the most fulfilling things I've ever done in ministry.

19:54.738 --> 19:57.266
And this story actually begins years ago.

19:57.346 --> 20:01.510
I was just starting out as an online pastor trying to figure out what that even meant.

20:01.530 --> 20:09.336
And there was a story that we were gonna share on the weekend about a bar in Wisconsin that during COVID would show our services on Monday evenings.

20:09.356 --> 20:17.363
We had the idea, well, what if other people are doing this as well and we just don't know about it or better yet, what if we invited people to do this in their communities?

20:17.764 --> 20:22.067
A way that they could leverage the online service to reach their neighbors with the gospel.

20:22.488 --> 20:27.332
And so we thought we could gather and show it in living rooms and coffee shops and movie theater

20:27.312 --> 20:33.357
as a conference rooms, and we wanted to call them something very obvious so that people would understand what they are.

20:33.678 --> 20:36.440
So these groups of people would view the service together.

20:36.600 --> 20:45.148
So viewing groups were really good at this, but right before we announced to the entire church, I had this vivid moment of doubt.

20:45.688 --> 20:50.593
I was sitting behind my desk, I put my head down, and I was thinking, this is just too simple.

20:51.113 --> 20:56.818
Basically, we're challenging people to turn on their TV and invite their neighbors to watch it with them.

20:56.898 --> 20:59.121
Like there's no way that this actually works.

20:59.741 --> 21:03.546
And sure enough, dozens of people reached out to start a group of their own.

21:03.646 --> 21:07.811
And one of those couples was Randin and Emily Ruggles from Southwest Florida.

21:08.191 --> 21:09.753
Their group continued to grow.

21:10.133 --> 21:12.917
Other amazing leaders stepped up to support them.

21:13.197 --> 21:16.461
And now we have three viewing groups in Southwest Florida.

21:16.761 --> 21:18.623
Fast forward to last weekend.

21:18.643 --> 21:23.229
Our online team had the privilege of going to see what God was doing in person.

21:23.589 --> 21:24.530
We got to meet them.

21:24.706 --> 21:25.767
Hang out with them.

21:25.787 --> 21:32.855
Hear the stories of how God has transformed their lives, and then we went to the ocean to baptize 26 of them.

21:33.476 --> 21:37.601
Before this viewing group started, many of them had never even heard of Eagle Brook.

21:37.901 --> 21:44.068
Some had barely ever attended church, and through the viewing groups, God has totally transformed their lives.

21:44.108 --> 21:48.914
And last weekend, they got to declare their faith in Jesus in the ocean through baptism.

21:49.538 --> 21:58.012
What was once just an idea being discussed in a conference room, today has become a tool that God has used to transform people's lives.

21:58.633 --> 22:05.905
If you live outside of driving distance of one of our campuses, I want to invite you to start a viewing group of your own.

22:06.346 --> 22:10.994
Leverage our weekend services to reach your neighbors with the gospel.

22:11.074 --> 22:19.527
We have learned a lot over the years about what makes these groups successful and would love a chance to connect with you to see what that could look like in your community.

22:19.928 --> 22:25.637
To let us know you're interested, head to Eaglebrookchurch.com, scroll down and click on the viewing group tile.

22:26.118 --> 22:33.810
And as you're doing that, I'm going to hand it over to Jason for today's message.

23:19.362 --> 23:20.163
I was in seminary.

23:20.263 --> 23:24.748
I volunteered at a nursing home as a part of a pastoral care class that I was in.

23:24.808 --> 23:29.493
And so on the first day, I kind of want to make a good impression or a button-up shirt, khakis.

23:29.894 --> 23:30.474
I got there.

23:30.514 --> 23:33.678
It was 96 degrees in the nursing home.

23:33.718 --> 23:35.260
I was sweating like crazy.

23:35.660 --> 23:44.410
The chaplain walked me around to introduce me to the residents and the first woman he introduced me to took one look at me and she said, comb your hair.

23:44.430 --> 23:48.434
This is a picture of what I look like back then.

23:49.314 --> 23:57.604
So she had a little bit of a point, and I don't know why I did this, but I tried to explain to her that it wasn't messy, it's just a style.

23:57.824 --> 23:59.806
I said, this is how people are wearing their hair these days.

24:00.587 --> 24:04.532
She looked at me and she said, that's not a style, that's just messy looking.

24:05.913 --> 24:08.957
And I was irritated, but I took the high road, I said, do you want a piece of me?

24:11.880 --> 24:13.362
But then the chaplain,

24:13.634 --> 24:19.862
told her that I was a seminary student who was gonna be volunteering at the nursing home and she looked at me and this is what she said.

24:20.182 --> 24:24.628
She said, and you call yourself religious with hair like that.

24:27.211 --> 24:28.793
How can you tell if someone's a Christian?

24:30.134 --> 24:30.935
Is it by their hair?

24:32.097 --> 24:33.338
Is it by their clothes?

24:33.438 --> 24:34.960
Is it by the words that they use?

24:35.000 --> 24:39.666
If they use big words like sanctification and consubstantiation, do you know what they're a Christian?

24:40.322 --> 24:42.044
I was listening to a podcast recently.

24:42.064 --> 24:44.668
It was a person who was Catholic, a person who was Jewish.

24:45.088 --> 24:50.996
And to listen to them talk, you would think that to be a Christian means to observe certain religious rituals.

24:52.458 --> 24:52.959
That's what it means.

24:52.999 --> 24:57.044
It goes to go to church, observe other certain religious rituals.

24:57.205 --> 24:58.947
Is that how you can tell?

24:59.888 --> 25:04.234
In the New Testament, Jesus refers to those who follow him, not as Christians.

25:04.314 --> 25:06.818
That term came later in the book of Acts.

25:07.198 --> 25:10.162
Jesus refers to his followers as disciples.

25:10.978 --> 25:13.701
Now the word disciple was not unique to Jesus.

25:13.761 --> 25:18.947
John the Baptist had disciples, other rabbis had disciples.

25:19.027 --> 25:24.973
In fact, in the New Testament, the Greek word for disciple is used 261 times.

25:26.515 --> 25:31.400
The literal translation means to be an apprentice or a learner.

25:32.201 --> 25:36.506
In ancient Jewish culture, formal education for little boys began about six years of age.

25:36.606 --> 25:40.370
So Jewish boys were enrolled in their local synagogue school

25:40.578 --> 25:50.573
called Bet Sufer, and they would begin to memorize the first five books of the Bible, Genesis, Exodus, of Leviticus, Numbers, and Deuteronomy.

25:51.695 --> 25:56.101
Can you imagine a six-year-old memorizing the book of Leviticus?

25:57.463 --> 26:07.218
Once they would graduate, they would move on to what was called Bet Talmud, where from the age of 10 to 14, they would memorize the rest of the Old Testament.

26:08.418 --> 26:12.644
The best of the best would then graduate to what was called bet midrash.

26:13.425 --> 26:15.508
Now many of them didn't graduate to that level.

26:15.768 --> 26:18.973
They would simply then go into the family business, go into fishing, something like that.

26:19.734 --> 26:25.021
But for the best of the best, they would move into bet midrash and there they would choose a rabbi.

26:26.082 --> 26:29.387
They would choose someone that they wanted to learn from and to follow.

26:29.708 --> 26:37.298
And if that rabbi believed that this person was worthy of their time and their attention, they would formally invite them to follow him.

26:38.242 --> 26:39.824
by saying these words, come and follow me.

26:41.386 --> 26:47.474
And when they said those words, that person, if they chose to follow, would become that rabbi's disciple.

26:48.315 --> 26:50.958
That meant that they spent every waking moment with that person.

26:51.960 --> 26:53.381
They would go where the rabbi went.

26:53.482 --> 26:54.583
They did what he did.

26:54.663 --> 26:58.288
They would listen to everything that he said.

26:59.449 --> 27:03.555
In other words, a disciple is not just someone who believes God exists.

27:05.077 --> 27:06.258
Satan believes that.

27:07.426 --> 27:08.487
I'll talk to people sometimes.

27:08.507 --> 27:09.548
I'll say, yeah, I'm a Christian.

27:10.029 --> 27:10.690
I believe in God.

27:10.710 --> 27:12.431
I've always believed that there's a God.

27:13.453 --> 27:17.437
And what I want to say in that moment is, Satan knows that there's a God.

27:18.158 --> 27:19.800
Satan believes that there's a God.

27:19.960 --> 27:20.721
He knows this.

27:20.941 --> 27:25.606
He knows that Jesus is the Son of God, but Satan is not a disciple.

27:27.128 --> 27:29.470
A disciple is not just someone who believes that God exists.

27:29.750 --> 27:33.074
A disciple is not someone who just goes to church when they have some time.

27:34.274 --> 27:37.678
They're not a person who's a good person or a moral person.

27:38.799 --> 27:40.301
Here's what a disciple is.

27:40.421 --> 27:45.066
A disciple very simply is a person who follows Jesus Christ.

27:46.568 --> 27:51.913
When Jesus says, come and follow me, it's a person who says, yes, I will follow.

27:52.874 --> 27:55.477
That means that when it comes to decisions like, who should I date?

27:55.978 --> 27:57.259
What should I do this weekend?

27:57.319 --> 27:58.581
How should I spend my money?

27:58.921 --> 28:03.346
They would look to Jesus and his word to answer those questions.

28:04.002 --> 28:17.895
In Jesus' time, there was a phrase covered in the dust of his rabbi and referred to a disciple who was walking so closely behind his rabbi that the dust from the rabbi's heels would begin to kick up on him.

28:18.576 --> 28:21.619
And so they would say, you are covered in the dust of your rabbi.

28:22.620 --> 28:25.142
Here's the question I wanna ask you.

28:25.162 --> 28:27.545
Are you covered in the dust of your rabbi?

28:29.166 --> 28:33.010
Are you walking that close to Jesus?

28:33.858 --> 28:37.804
All this brings us to Matthew 28, the verse we've been focused on in this series.

28:37.824 --> 28:40.808
What we've said is this verse is our one job as Christians.

28:41.990 --> 28:48.620
That this verse is the message, the mission that Jesus gave to every single follower of Christ.

28:49.702 --> 28:57.113
When Vince Lombardi stood in front of his football team for the first time in 1961 at training camp, he held up a football.

28:58.054 --> 29:00.498
He said, gentlemen, this is a football.

29:01.538 --> 29:04.984
His point was, we're getting back to the basics.

29:05.004 --> 29:06.907
We're gonna get back to the fundamentals.

29:07.869 --> 29:10.073
And that's what we've been trying to do in this series.

29:10.093 --> 29:11.395
Let's go back to the basics.

29:11.615 --> 29:14.560
Let's go back to the fundamentals of our faith.

29:15.282 --> 29:16.945
Here's what Jesus said in Matthew 28.

29:18.908 --> 29:21.012
Jesus came to them, that's his disciples.

29:22.254 --> 29:27.122
And he said this, all authority in heaven and on earth has been given to me.

29:28.450 --> 29:30.273
It's important because the next word is therefore.

29:30.313 --> 29:32.756
So in light of that authority, here's what he says to us.

29:33.317 --> 29:35.120
Go and make disciples.

29:37.143 --> 29:39.827
This is the mission of every single follower of Christ.

29:40.167 --> 29:52.886
Go make disciples of all nations, baptizing them in the name of the Father and the Son and of the Holy Spirit and teaching them to obey everything I have commanded you.

29:53.748 --> 29:54.589
Notice the verbs here.

29:56.031 --> 29:58.034
Go, baptize.

29:58.466 --> 29:58.927
Make.

30:00.648 --> 30:04.613
I know what it means to go, and I know what it means to baptize, but here's the question.

30:04.993 --> 30:07.116
What does it mean to make a disciple?

30:08.397 --> 30:10.960
As I was writing this message, I thought, are people gonna care about this?

30:11.841 --> 30:16.747
I mean, you might be struggling with anxiety, you might have financial struggles, you might be trying to raise kids.

30:17.147 --> 30:21.132
Is making disciples, is that even in the top 10 list of things you're thinking about?

30:22.233 --> 30:24.195
You could see why that wouldn't be the case.

30:25.416 --> 30:26.898
Let me try to persuade you.

30:27.618 --> 30:30.041
In his book, True Disciples, George Barnas says this.

30:31.343 --> 30:34.087
He says, following Jesus isn't a program.

30:35.409 --> 30:36.610
It's not a worship service.

30:37.672 --> 30:39.655
It's not a class that you take.

30:39.715 --> 30:40.296
Here's what it is.

30:40.656 --> 30:42.999
It's a lifelong adventure.

30:44.381 --> 30:50.049
It affects how you think the decisions you make and how you relate to others.

30:52.352 --> 30:53.714
I want to be a better leader.

30:54.690 --> 31:01.737
I wanna be a better husband, I wanna be a better father, I wanna think better, and not just better, I wanna think like Jesus thought.

31:02.978 --> 31:05.201
I wanna love people like Jesus loved people.

31:05.541 --> 31:08.204
I want to live like Jesus lived.

31:09.305 --> 31:13.028
Wouldn't you want that for the people that you love, the people that you're around every day?

31:14.330 --> 31:17.733
If you wanna make a difference in our world, make disciples.

31:19.074 --> 31:22.738
If you wanna be a great mom, a great dad, disciple your kids,

31:23.970 --> 31:34.386
If you wanna have a purpose for your life, make disciples, you might be here today and think, I'm just an accountant, I sell insurance, I'm a teacher, I'm a coach, here's what you really are.

31:34.706 --> 31:36.929
You are in the disciple making business.

31:38.732 --> 31:42.898
You are in the disciple making business just as much as I am in the disciple making business.

31:43.179 --> 31:45.562
To be a follower of Jesus Christ.

31:46.384 --> 31:50.430
To be a disciple of Jesus Christ is to make other disciples.

31:51.511 --> 31:53.234
Let me show you two characteristics.

31:53.442 --> 31:55.264
of a disciple or a follower of Christ.

31:55.304 --> 32:00.130
The first one is this, they know and they obey the voice of God.

32:01.312 --> 32:03.855
If you're wondering, what does it mean to be a follower of Christ?

32:03.875 --> 32:08.260
They are a person who knows and they obey God's voice.

32:09.221 --> 32:11.985
Jesus told a parable one time in John 10 as a story.

32:12.265 --> 32:15.489
And in the story, he was the shepherd and we were the sheep.

32:16.410 --> 32:19.394
And here's what he says about his followers who are the sheep in this story.

32:19.694 --> 32:22.898
He said, the shepherd's sheep follow him.

32:24.418 --> 32:27.341
So right away, it's a disciple following his rabbi.

32:27.581 --> 32:28.962
They're going where he went.

32:29.303 --> 32:31.044
They follow him and why do they do that?

32:32.446 --> 32:35.068
Because they know his voice.

32:37.190 --> 32:39.172
Do you know God's voice?

32:41.214 --> 32:43.737
I had someone ask me this question recently that, but how do you know?

32:43.937 --> 32:45.759
I mean, how do you know it's just not your own thoughts?

32:45.999 --> 32:47.500
How do you know it's God's voice?

32:48.381 --> 32:53.426
And they had listened to a sermon from another pastor and he was telling a story about a time he was praying.

32:54.498 --> 33:02.167
And he had this like 20 minute conversation with God, where it was like this kind of flippant, joking, back and forth between him and God.

33:03.048 --> 33:06.932
And so he was like, you know, I'm not gonna do that God and God's, you know, you're not so important to me.

33:07.193 --> 33:10.717
And it was like this big, funny, like 20 minute little flippant conversation.

33:12.359 --> 33:18.706
Now maybe he was just embellishing the story a little bit, but when I hear pastors talk like that, I get worried.

33:19.650 --> 33:26.459
And the reason that I get worried is because it sets the expectation that if you're hearing from God, that's how you'll hear from Him.

33:29.062 --> 33:34.368
It lends the impression that, well, maybe the pastor is hearing from God in a way that's not available to me.

33:35.710 --> 33:37.052
And that's simply not true.

33:38.253 --> 33:45.202
I have never had a 20 minute flippant, funny, little back and forth with Almighty Holy God.

33:46.914 --> 33:49.878
When God speaks to me, here's often how I hear his voice.

33:50.238 --> 33:51.420
Often it's through Scripture.

33:52.381 --> 34:01.513
I'll read a verse in the Bible and I'll think about it and I'll meditate on it and I'll realize God is using that verse to speak to me in a certain situation in my life.

34:03.435 --> 34:04.056
You got to get this.

34:04.336 --> 34:08.882
God will never say something to you that contradicts what he said in the Bible.

34:10.914 --> 34:13.258
If you hear something from God and you're like, oh, I think that's God.

34:13.458 --> 34:17.824
And then you read it in the Bible and it contradicts what you thought that you heard that wasn't God.

34:18.886 --> 34:23.413
God will never say something to you that contradicts what he has already said.

34:24.695 --> 34:29.722
But sometimes one of the ways I will hear from God is I'll have a thought or someone else will speak to me.

34:30.343 --> 34:33.508
And that doesn't mean that every thought or everything that people say is from God.

34:33.749 --> 34:37.394
But here's what I've come to realize over the years as I've gotten to know God.

34:38.114 --> 34:44.943
As I've read the Bible, as I've prayed, as I've followed Him and spent time with Him, over time, I've come to know His voice.

34:46.285 --> 34:50.530
If you know God, you often begin to know His voice.

34:51.271 --> 34:56.418
I've told this story before, but several years ago, I got pulled over on 35W in the middle of rush hour traffic.

34:56.478 --> 35:00.844
And I'll just tell you, if you're a pastor of a church and you get pulled over in rush hour, here's what you do.

35:01.145 --> 35:02.226
You look the other way.

35:02.818 --> 35:07.743
You pretend like that guardrail is the most interesting thing you have ever seen in your entire life.

35:07.804 --> 35:10.206
I mean, people are not seeing the front of my face.

35:10.226 --> 35:16.113
They might see the back, but I'm gonna look over here because I don't want people driving by and go, that's my pastor.

35:16.713 --> 35:19.136
Got pulled over and then freeway right there.

35:19.737 --> 35:22.340
So I'm looking the other way.

35:22.440 --> 35:24.922
The next day, my mom called me on the phone.

35:26.544 --> 35:29.668
She said, did you get pulled over on 35W yesterday?

35:29.708 --> 35:31.730
This is my 80 year old mom.

35:32.898 --> 35:34.761
And I said to her, yeah, I did.

35:34.801 --> 35:40.870
And then in a rather happy and excited tone, she said, I knew it.

35:42.192 --> 35:43.854
I drove past and I saw the car.

35:43.914 --> 35:45.276
I thought, Jason has that car.

35:45.777 --> 35:49.122
And then I drove past and I saw the back of your head and I knew it was you.

35:49.162 --> 35:57.314
Now, I don't know many people who have been pulled over in front of their 80 year old mom.

35:58.656 --> 36:00.178
But why did my mom know me?

36:01.474 --> 36:02.335
Well, why did she know it was me?

36:02.355 --> 36:03.738
Well, because she knows me.

36:03.778 --> 36:06.121
She could recognize me.

36:07.243 --> 36:09.246
Maybe today you are turning your head from God.

36:10.969 --> 36:12.772
There's something that you don't want God to see.

36:12.812 --> 36:14.815
You certainly don't want other people to see it.

36:15.116 --> 36:15.957
You are hiding it.

36:16.197 --> 36:18.421
You are turning from God.

36:20.304 --> 36:21.085
God knows you.

36:22.668 --> 36:29.138
The Bible says he knows the number of hairs on the back of your head.

36:29.218 --> 36:34.063
knows you and not only does he know you, he wants you to know his voice.

36:34.944 --> 36:40.170
And not only does he want you to know his voice, he wants you to obey his voice.

36:40.930 --> 36:44.194
When my son Hudson was three years old, he used to get out of bed all the time at night.

36:44.554 --> 36:47.437
And so there was this one night, I put him back into bed three different times.

36:48.058 --> 36:52.102
And I told him, I said, hey, you get out of bed again, you are gonna get a big consequence.

36:53.003 --> 36:55.666
And I didn't tell him what the consequence was because I didn't know.

36:56.610 --> 36:58.272
This is my whole parenting philosophy.

36:58.352 --> 36:58.813
I bluff.

36:59.033 --> 37:00.154
I bluff all the time.

37:00.615 --> 37:02.357
Sometimes they call your bluff, sometimes they don't.

37:03.258 --> 37:17.456
And so about an hour later, I was walking up to go to bed and there's Hudson sitting on the steps, top of the steps like this, half asleep, and he looks down and he sees me start coming up the stairs and I'm coming in hot.

37:17.576 --> 37:18.938
I mean, I'm not happy.

37:19.319 --> 37:25.266
And so he kind of jumps up and he looks over at me and I get to him and he goes, oh, daddy, daddy, daddy, daddy, daddy.

37:27.298 --> 37:28.740
You the best daddy ever.

37:28.800 --> 37:34.408
And I thought, wow, thank you, son.

37:34.868 --> 37:38.012
I really appreciate that encouragement.

37:38.053 --> 37:40.316
But here's what I really wanted him to do.

37:40.336 --> 37:42.218
I wanted him to obey me.

37:42.238 --> 37:46.284
I didn't just want him to tell me I was the best dad ever that he loved me.

37:46.464 --> 37:48.487
I wanted him to obey me.

37:48.547 --> 37:56.978
Second John says this, this is love that we walk in obedience to his commands.

37:58.946 --> 38:06.736
And we can say, well, God, I love you, but really what demonstrates our love is when we walk in obedience to His commands.

38:07.917 --> 38:14.846
It doesn't mean that we're perfect, but it means there's a desire in our life to obey God, to obey His voice.

38:15.967 --> 38:21.714
James, chapter two says this, but if someone will say, you have faith, I have works.

38:22.498 --> 38:25.443
Like, well, you know, one person has faith, one person has works, you know, it doesn't really matter.

38:25.683 --> 38:26.264
Someone will say that.

38:26.585 --> 38:29.650
Here's what James says, show me your faith without your works.

38:30.692 --> 38:33.576
And I will show you my faith by my works.

38:35.400 --> 38:38.485
This is such an important theological concept.

38:38.745 --> 38:44.795
The Bible makes it clear, we are saved by God's grace through faith in Jesus Christ.

38:44.815 --> 38:46.338
That is how a person is saved.

38:46.358 --> 38:48.882
They are not saved by good works.

38:49.954 --> 38:56.100
But if you have faith in Jesus Christ, your works will demonstrate your faith.

38:57.742 --> 39:02.226
Your works will be a byproduct of your faith in Jesus Christ.

39:02.267 --> 39:03.528
Your works don't save you.

39:04.449 --> 39:10.455
But your works will show and illustrate the faith that you have.

39:10.515 --> 39:11.576
Here's what a disciple does.

39:11.836 --> 39:15.920
They know God's voice and they want to obey God's voice.

39:16.401 --> 39:17.522
Here's the second characteristic.

39:18.370 --> 39:20.513
a disciple makes disciples.

39:21.835 --> 39:31.970
Paul in 1 Corinthians says this, he says, my goal is to find common ground with everyone that I meet so that I might bring them to Christ.

39:34.154 --> 39:36.417
What if this week you sat down and said, this is my goal?

39:37.699 --> 39:45.170
Every new person that I meet, every person I encounter, my goal is to build some common ground with them

39:46.434 --> 39:51.220
for the purpose that I could lead them to faith in Jesus Christ.

39:52.081 --> 39:53.723
And my son Hudson was 12 years old.

39:54.144 --> 40:00.652
He was out at a restaurant with a friend and he asked the waitress, he said, what are some of the like pops and lemonades that you would recommend?

40:00.672 --> 40:01.914
They had some different ones on the menu.

40:02.495 --> 40:06.540
And she goes, oh, high fructose corn syrup, I don't touch that stuff.

40:06.560 --> 40:08.402
Wasn't exactly selling her product real well.

40:08.783 --> 40:14.290
Then she went on a rant about vitamin D and vitamin C and the importance of that in your life.

40:14.882 --> 40:17.285
So my son said, well, he should meet my health teacher.

40:18.346 --> 40:19.708
She goes, is he single?

40:22.931 --> 40:24.453
And my son goes, actually he is.

40:25.615 --> 40:28.298
Now Hudson was telling me this story and I was like, wow, this is perfect.

40:28.318 --> 40:30.320
Like this actually sounds really good.

40:30.340 --> 40:31.742
And he goes, well, she had a mullet.

40:34.245 --> 40:35.366
I said, why is that a negative?

40:35.406 --> 40:40.452
I mean, she's taking your order, all professional, then when she turns around, she's letting you know.

40:40.472 --> 40:42.194
You're gonna have a good time tonight, okay?

40:42.466 --> 40:43.628
It's going to be a good time.

40:43.648 --> 40:44.990
I said, that's not a negative at all.

40:45.752 --> 40:48.737
But here was the cool part of the conversation.

40:48.757 --> 40:53.806
She said, when I became a Christian last year, I started to get healthy in all areas of my life.

40:54.948 --> 40:57.192
And my son, 12 years old, he goes, oh, I'm a Christian.

40:57.252 --> 40:58.173
My friends are Christian.

40:58.193 --> 40:58.995
She goes, you are.

41:00.257 --> 41:05.566
She said, I get so excited when I hear young people today who are following Jesus.

41:06.828 --> 41:07.890
And I'm the same way.

41:08.994 --> 41:15.242
I get so excited when I talk to a teenager or a young adult who loves Jesus, it just fires me up.

41:16.824 --> 41:24.914
Gen Z, this generation of young people, is turning to Christ like no other generation in the last several decades.

41:24.934 --> 41:26.376
I mean, just read the statistics.

41:26.696 --> 41:34.386
Church attendance is up and it's Gen Z. Gen Z is the one who's attending church more than any other demographic or generation.

41:35.266 --> 41:36.388
They're buying Bibles.

41:36.668 --> 41:37.830
They're reading the Bible.

41:38.050 --> 41:39.292
They are pursuing God.

41:39.552 --> 41:43.598
This generation is hungry for God in their life and it just excites me.

41:44.719 --> 41:45.901
I got an email this week.

41:47.283 --> 41:51.128
When we baptized people, we asked them to write out their testimony of how they came to Christ.

41:52.250 --> 41:53.472
And this is what this guy wrote.

41:53.492 --> 41:54.734
He said, I didn't grow up religious.

41:54.934 --> 41:58.619
I always thought that something big would have to happen in my life for me to come to Christ.

41:59.821 --> 42:03.506
He said, within two weeks of each other, my grandpa passed away.

42:04.162 --> 42:06.306
And my girlfriend of five years broke up with me.

42:07.908 --> 42:09.932
He said, I was struggling to find purpose in life.

42:10.072 --> 42:11.915
Each day felt repetitive and empty.

42:13.939 --> 42:15.662
When I was an unbeliever, that's how my life felt.

42:17.585 --> 42:18.807
It's just repetitive, it's empty.

42:20.190 --> 42:22.854
He said, there wasn't a major fallout between me and my girlfriend.

42:22.874 --> 42:25.739
The main issue was I wasn't religious and she was.

42:26.180 --> 42:29.586
We broke up in the parking lot at Bethel University where she attended school.

42:30.402 --> 42:34.547
And the last thing she told me was this, buy a Bible and go to Eaglebrook Church.

42:36.670 --> 42:37.310
I like this girl.

42:40.815 --> 42:46.561
He said on May 18th, 2025, so almost a year ago, he said, I went to church for the first time in my life.

42:48.263 --> 42:49.124
And I went alone.

42:50.646 --> 42:52.769
That day, Jason, me was speaking.

42:53.690 --> 42:57.074
The series was on the book of Revelation, which he said was confusing to me.

42:57.698 --> 43:00.301
He has a tough one, first time ever in church, you're in a series on Revelation.

43:00.862 --> 43:03.004
But he said, Jason shared his personal testimony.

43:03.044 --> 43:06.208
He talked about how while he was in college, he wasn't a believer.

43:06.529 --> 43:08.871
He went to visit his girlfriend who was a Christian.

43:09.432 --> 43:14.378
Unknowingly, she had planned to break up with him, ended the relationship, gave him a pamphlet about the Bible.

43:15.339 --> 43:18.423
And a few days later, he broke down and gave his life to Jesus.

43:19.905 --> 43:24.370
Hearing Jason's testimony felt impossible to ignore, the similarities were undeniable.

43:24.962 --> 43:29.446
He could have shared that testimony any other week of the year, but he shared it that day.

43:30.307 --> 43:35.212
Right after I had gone through the near same exact experience, I don't believe that was a coincidence.

43:36.213 --> 43:39.096
From that moment forward, I gave my life to Jesus.

43:40.077 --> 43:46.723
A few weeks later, my girlfriend and I met again to talk everything through, we got back together, began attending Eagle Brook together every week.

43:47.184 --> 43:50.727
On December 30th, I asked her to marry me and we got engaged.

43:52.028 --> 43:53.810
He said, thanks again, Jason.

43:54.114 --> 43:55.016
Well, you're welcome.

44:02.489 --> 44:05.635
When they have children, I think Jason would be a perfect name.

44:06.616 --> 44:09.942
I'm just going to throw that out there for them.

44:09.962 --> 44:12.727
But I was reading that email in my office.

44:12.747 --> 44:13.469
I was choked up.

44:15.352 --> 44:18.738
I was just choked up that God would use my life and my story

44:18.850 --> 44:24.017
and that God would take someone who's going through something similar and go, I'm gonna have you be in church this weekend.

44:25.219 --> 44:34.151
And I'm gonna have you hear this testimony right at this moment in your life because I love you and I want to draw you to myself.

44:34.171 --> 44:40.500
And when I hear stories like that, I get so excited and I want everyone in our church to experience that.

44:42.002 --> 44:47.570
I want everyone in our church to know how to share your faith in Jesus, how to make disciples.

44:48.514 --> 44:52.560
And I talk to people all the time and we're like, I know I should tell people about Jesus.

44:52.640 --> 44:54.082
I know I wanna talk more about Jesus.

44:54.463 --> 44:55.364
I just don't know what to say.

44:56.325 --> 44:57.667
I just don't know what to say.

44:58.889 --> 45:02.655
And I'm gonna show you a way that you can share your faith with someone.

45:02.695 --> 45:07.702
This is what someone shared with me when I was a non-believer and it made sense.

45:07.722 --> 45:10.085
And this is just one tool, you don't have to do this.

45:10.125 --> 45:16.114
In fact, most conversations, I'm just trying to build some common ground and use that to lead a person to Jesus.

45:17.282 --> 45:19.886
But if you're wondering, you're like, well, how would I share my faith?

45:19.926 --> 45:22.571
Let me try to show you what this person shared with me.

45:22.611 --> 45:23.472
Here's what they shared with me.

45:23.512 --> 45:29.502
They said, you are over here and there is a gap between you and God.

45:29.542 --> 45:30.324
Sorry for my drawing.

45:31.906 --> 45:34.030
There's a gap between you and God and here's the gap.

45:35.452 --> 45:35.853
It's sin.

45:38.157 --> 45:39.920
Now at this point, here's what a lot of people do.

45:39.940 --> 45:41.322
They'll go, well, I don't know.

45:41.442 --> 45:43.826
I'm not really sure if I have sinned.

45:44.706 --> 45:46.810
And this is where it's good to know some Bible verses.

45:46.850 --> 45:50.957
Romans 3, 23 says, all have sinned and fallen short of the glory of God.

45:52.219 --> 45:56.065
There is not a single person who has never sinned before.

45:56.125 --> 45:59.271
If you're here today and you're like, I don't think I've ever sinned before.

45:59.451 --> 46:00.693
You're lying, that's a sin.

46:04.399 --> 46:10.770
And so what I will explain to the person is I will say, this sin creates a gap between you and God.

46:12.322 --> 46:16.406
And then I will take them to Romans 6, 23, the wages of sin is death.

46:17.668 --> 46:22.152
A wage is something you earn, it's something you've deserved.

46:22.172 --> 46:29.440
So the wage of our sin is death, that is physical death one day, but it's also spiritual death and separation from God as well.

46:30.701 --> 46:39.250
Now here's what people will say to me often at this point, they'll say, well, I've made some mistakes, done some things I shouldn't have done, but it seems kind of harsh, that the penalty for that would be death.

46:40.322 --> 46:44.108
And what I will point out to them is every time you sin, it creates this gap.

46:46.491 --> 46:50.617
If you sin against your kids, it will create a gap between you and your son or your daughter.

46:52.160 --> 46:56.165
If you sin against your spouse, it will create a gap in your marriage.

46:57.207 --> 47:03.496
If you sin a big sin against your spouse, it will create a huge gap and separation in that relationship.

47:04.518 --> 47:05.479
It's the same way with God.

47:06.741 --> 47:10.066
When we sin against God, it creates separation.

47:10.914 --> 47:11.796
But here's the difference.

47:11.876 --> 47:13.799
God is not just another human being.

47:14.881 --> 47:15.763
God is infinite.

47:15.964 --> 47:16.785
He is holy.

47:17.026 --> 47:20.973
And so when we sin against Him, the gap that it creates is infinite.

47:22.215 --> 47:27.265
You can't just say, well, I'm going to go to the food shelf and volunteer a few hours and I'll kind of close that gap.

47:27.525 --> 47:31.513
There's no amount of good works that can close that gap between you and God.

47:32.996 --> 47:34.258
And so God took the initiative.

47:35.362 --> 47:42.971
Romans 5, 8 says, he demonstrates his love for us that while we were still sinners, Christ died for us.

47:44.813 --> 47:45.734
It's the cross.

47:47.036 --> 47:50.760
It's the cross of Jesus Christ that bridges that gap.

47:50.780 --> 47:52.663
It's why this is called the bridge analogy.

47:53.604 --> 47:56.828
And how do you walk across that bridge?

47:57.769 --> 47:58.770
Romans 10,

47:59.362 --> 48:06.771
9 says that if you confess with your lips and you believe in your heart that Jesus Christ is Lord, you will be saved.

48:07.792 --> 48:09.274
You can share this with anyone.

48:09.935 --> 48:12.918
You can draw this out on a napkin.

48:12.938 --> 48:22.610
If you just know these verses that all have sinned and fallen short of the glory of God, Romans 3, 23, Romans 6, 23, the wages of sin is death with the free gift of God as eternal life through Jesus Christ.

48:23.298 --> 48:27.223
Romans 5, 8, God demonstrates His love for us, that while we're still sinners, Christ died for us.

48:27.443 --> 48:31.969
Romans 10, 9, if you confess with your lips, believe in your heart, Jesus Christ is Lord, you will be safe.

48:32.209 --> 48:37.856
You memorize those four verses and you know how to just draw this out and explain how a person gets to Jesus.

48:38.236 --> 48:41.681
You can share your faith and lead another person to Christ.

48:42.602 --> 48:45.305
Now maybe you're watching this, you're like, I don't know if I'll remember all that.

48:45.946 --> 48:47.187
We have a QR code for you.

48:48.048 --> 48:50.812
QR code coming up on the screen here, I hope in just a moment.

48:51.933 --> 48:52.594
There it is.

48:53.058 --> 48:55.221
grab your phone, you can grab that.

48:55.261 --> 48:57.765
If you're online, we'll have that up after church.

48:58.366 --> 49:00.830
So when the service is over, you can just stay in your seat and pull that up.

49:01.170 --> 49:09.944
It will have this drawing and the verses that I just laid out so that you have it on your phone and you can be ready and prepared.

49:11.005 --> 49:15.151
If all else fails, invite a person to church.

49:16.293 --> 49:22.162
I had lunch with a couple of friends recently who go to our church and afterwards my wife said, do you remember how they started coming?

49:22.594 --> 49:23.936
And I was like, no, I actually don't.

49:23.976 --> 49:24.737
It was like 10 years ago.

49:24.757 --> 49:27.079
And she said, our daughter Isabel was six years old.

49:28.181 --> 49:30.343
And she was in the kids ministry here at Eagle Brook.

49:30.384 --> 49:31.545
And they gave out suckers.

49:31.645 --> 49:33.768
And I don't remember why the whole connection to suckers.

49:34.108 --> 49:36.571
But they gave out a sucker and said, use this to invite someone to church.

49:37.733 --> 49:39.975
And so later that day, we were at a basketball tournament.

49:40.236 --> 49:42.719
Us and this other family, our sons were on the same basketball team.

49:43.079 --> 49:47.605
And Isabel, six years old, walked up to this family and said, would you like to go to church?

49:47.625 --> 49:48.205
Here's a sucker.

49:50.788 --> 49:52.050
And they said, yeah.

49:52.802 --> 49:54.024
We've been thinking about going to church.

49:54.064 --> 49:54.484
We'll come.

49:55.265 --> 49:58.310
And so they started coming to church and God got ahold of their life.

49:58.630 --> 50:08.264
And the wife at one point texted my wife and she said, I've been reading through the Bible in a year and God is spiritually moving in our family and in our heart and in our lives.

50:08.344 --> 50:14.953
And all it took was a six year old girl walking up and going, would you come to church?

50:16.074 --> 50:18.658
Next weekend we are starting a new series called Encounters with Jesus.

50:19.519 --> 50:21.522
We've been planning and working on this series

50:21.634 --> 50:22.696
for months.

50:23.597 --> 50:28.325
Our prayer and our hope is that people wouldn't just know about Jesus, but that they would know Him.

50:28.385 --> 50:35.096
That they wouldn't just hear about Him, but that they would encounter Him and experience Him in their life.

50:35.397 --> 50:38.041
And next week's message is, will you follow Jesus?

50:39.544 --> 50:41.908
It is the perfect message to invite someone to.

50:42.228 --> 50:45.574
We are going to share the gospel and give people a chance to respond.

50:45.894 --> 50:48.018
Who is that person in your life that you could bring?

50:49.122 --> 51:00.457
Who is that person in your life that you could say, hey, I'll take you out to lunch, I'll take you out to dinner, just come to church, give it a lead up to Easter as you just spiritually give yourself some time to get to know Jesus leading up to Easter.

51:01.398 --> 51:05.183
But who is that person that you could invite to church next weekend?

51:05.324 --> 51:09.109
I believe that life and death are at stake.

51:09.970 --> 51:16.178
In 1912, there was a Scottish pastor named John Harper who boarded a ship called the Titanic with his daughter and his niece.

51:17.346 --> 51:18.547
He was headed to Chicago.

51:18.607 --> 51:21.371
He was going to speak at Moody Bible Church for over a month.

51:22.552 --> 51:28.799
And as you know, on April 14th, the Titanic hit an iceberg and it began to sink.

51:28.819 --> 51:35.567
John Harper put his daughter and his niece on a lifeboat, but then he gave up his spot for a woman.

51:37.389 --> 51:41.874
As his niece and his daughter were drifting away, his niece said that she looked up

51:43.522 --> 51:53.798
And she saw her uncle, John, on the deck of the Titanic, and he was saying to people, believe in Jesus and you will be saved.

51:53.818 --> 51:54.559
And she drifted away.

51:57.243 --> 52:00.007
Four years later, a man stood up at a church in Scotland.

52:01.670 --> 52:05.316
He said, I became a Christian the night the Titanic sunk.

52:07.198 --> 52:12.146
I was holding on to a piece of driftwood in the water, and this man, John Harper, drifted over towards me.

52:13.218 --> 52:14.881
And he asked me, he said, are you saved?

52:16.464 --> 52:18.267
And I said, no, sir, I don't believe that I am.

52:19.829 --> 52:22.394
And he said, believe in Jesus and you will be saved.

52:23.696 --> 52:27.883
And he said, then John Harper drifted away and on a wave and he came back a little bit later.

52:27.923 --> 52:28.945
He said, are you saved yet?

52:30.508 --> 52:32.050
He said, no, I don't think I am.

52:33.793 --> 52:36.979
Harper drifted away in another wave and the man never saw him again.

52:37.019 --> 52:38.802
His body sunk to the ocean floor.

52:40.738 --> 52:43.501
But he says, as I sat there holding onto this piece of drift to it.

52:45.363 --> 52:48.066
I can't even explain it, but God did something and I believed.

52:49.508 --> 52:57.757
And in that moment, the Holy Spirit came into my life and I believed that Jesus Christ died on the cross for my sins and I prayed to receive him into my life.

52:59.038 --> 53:01.881
He said, I was John Harper's last convert.

53:04.344 --> 53:06.066
Is there someone in your life who's drifting?

53:08.578 --> 53:10.981
Is there someone in your life who needs to be rescued?

53:14.385 --> 53:14.666
Go.

53:14.686 --> 53:18.951
Tell them about Jesus.

53:20.794 --> 53:21.895
Invite them to church.

53:21.975 --> 53:24.539
Do whatever it takes.

53:24.659 --> 53:27.022
Go and make disciples.

53:27.943 --> 53:29.084
Let's pray together as we close.

53:35.653 --> 53:36.594
Jesus right now,

53:38.498 --> 53:39.559
I pray for our church.

53:41.282 --> 53:49.413
I pray for every person here who is a follower of Jesus Christ, that this week an invitation would go out.

53:51.255 --> 53:53.719
And I'm in this as well, God, I'm doing this as well.

53:55.822 --> 54:01.970
God, would you bring a name to our mind right now of someone who's drifting spiritually and who needs you in their life?

54:02.914 --> 54:09.664
And God, would you give us the courage and the strength and the opportunity, God, to invite them this week?

54:09.684 --> 54:13.210
